ZH: 我们去清理家族墓碑。

EN: We went to clean the family tombstone.

ZH: 在黄昏时分，他站在朋友墓碑前默默祈祷。

EN: At dusk, he stood in front of his friend's tombstone praying silently.

ZH: 这座墓碑记载了他的生平。

EN: This tombstone records his life story.

ZH: 墓碑上刻着一行行的文字。

EN: The tombstone is engraved with rows of text.

ZH: 他们为逝去的爱人立起了墓碑。

EN: They erected a tombstone for their deceased loved one.

ZH: 这座墓碑包含了他的姓名和出生日期。

EN: This tombstone contains his name and date of birth.

ZH: 墓碑已经被岁月的侵蚀所损坏。

EN: The tombstone has been damaged by the erosion of time.

ZH: 他们在墓碑前放下一束鲜花。

EN: They placed a bouquet of flowers in front of the tombstone.

ZH: 这座非常古老的墓碑已经倾斜了很久。

EN: This very old tombstone has been leaning for a long time.

ZH: 他们在花园里建立了一座纪念墓碑。

EN: They built a memorial tombstone in the garden.

ZH: 墓碑被绿色的苔藓覆盖。

EN: The tombstone is covered with green moss.

ZH: 每个墓碑背后都有一段感人的故事。

EN: Behind every tombstone, there is a moving story.

ZH: 每逢清明节，他们都会来瞻仰父母的墓碑。

EN: Every Qingming Festival, they come to pay respects to their parents' tombstone.

ZH: 这座墓碑是为了纪念一位英勇的消防员而立。

EN: This tombstone was erected in memory of a brave firefighter.

ZH: 这面墙上雕刻了每位战士的名字，作为他们的墓碑。

EN: The names of every soldier are engraved on this wall as their tombstone.

ZH: 墓碑的上方飘着一面国旗。

EN: Above the tombstone flies a national flag.

ZH: 墓碑后面有一片寂静的墓地。

EN: Behind the tombstone lies a quiet graveyard.
